<exercise checkit-seed="0005" checkit-slug="AI3" checkit-title="Volumes of Revolution">
    <statement>
        <p>
            Consider the region bounded by <m>y=\frac{5}{2} \, x + 1, y=0,  x=2, x=5</m>.  
            
            <ol>
                <li>Find an integral which computes the volume of the solid formed by rotating this region about the <m>x</m>-axis.</li>
                <li>Find an integral which computes the volume of the solid formed by rotating this region about the <m>y</m>-axis.</li>
            </ol>
            
        </p>
        
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <p>
            <ol>
                <li>Using the washer/disk method, we obtain <me>\int_{ 2 }^{ 5 } \pi \left(\frac{5}{2} \, x + 1\right)^2dx</me> and using the shell method, we obtain 
                    <me>\int_0^{ 6 } 2\pi y\left( 5-2\right)dy +\int_{ 6 }^{ \frac{27}{2} } 2\pi y\left( 5-\left(\frac{2}{5} \, y - \frac{2}{5}\right)\right)dy.</me></li>
                
                
                <li>Using the washer/disk method, we obtain 
                    <me>\int_0^{ 6 } \pi\left(5^2-2^2\right)dy + \int_{ 6 }^{ \frac{27}{2} } \pi\left(5^2-\left(\frac{2}{5} \, y - \frac{2}{5}\right)^2\right)dy</me> and using the shell method, we obtain 
                    <me>\int_{ 2 }^{ 5 }2\pi x \left(\frac{5}{2} \, x + 1\right)dx.</me>
                </li>    
            </ol>
        </p>
    </answer>
</exercise>
